<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How much does dishwasher repair cost?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Our diagnostic fee is $89, applied toward the repair once you approve the work. Most dishwasher repairs run between $120 and $280. A door latch, water inlet valve, or detergent dispenser replacement is toward the lower end. Control board or wash pump replacements on premium brands like Miele, Bosch, or Thermador run higher. We provide a full written estimate before any work begins."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Which areas of Southern California do you cover?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "All five counties: Los Angeles, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, and Riverside. We dispatch from 8 service territories, West Hollywood (HQ), Los Angeles, Beverly Hills, Pasadena, Thousand Oaks, Irvine, Rancho Cucamonga, and Temecula, so the technician on your call is coming from the closest one. From Newport Beach to Pasadena to Thousand Oaks to Temecula, same-day is our standard."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "My dishwasher has standing water after the cycle, what's wrong?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Standing water after a cycle almost always points to the drain pump, either a failed pump motor or a clog in the pump filter or drain hose. On most dishwashers the filter is at the bottom of the tub and should be cleaned regularly. In SoCal's hard water environment, mineral deposits can coat the filter and pump components, accelerating buildup. We clean the filter and check the pump before any parts are replaced."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Why do my dishes come out cloudy or with a white film?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Across Southern California, this is almost always a hard water issue, not a dishwasher malfunction. SoCal's municipal water supplies, LADWP, MWD, Calleguas, Santa Margarita, Rancho California, run high in calcium and magnesium, harder than most US cities. Deposits leave a white film on glassware and dishes over time. The spray arms and water inlet valve can also accumulate mineral deposits that reduce washing performance. We inspect the spray arm ports, the inlet valve screen, and the detergent dispenser to make sure the machine itself is functioning correctly, then advise on whether a rinse aid or water softener product would address the residue."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do you repair panel-ready and integrated dishwashers?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. Panel-ready dishwashers with custom cabinet fronts, common in Beverly Hills, Newport Coast, Pacific Palisades, Pasadena estates, and renovated homes across SoCal, require extra care during access and disassembly. We know the correct procedure for removing the door panel without damaging the cabinetry, and we're familiar with the premium brands most often spec'd in these installations: Miele, Bosch, Thermador, Cove, and Gaggenau."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "My dishwasher won't start, what are the most common causes?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "The door latch is the most frequent culprit, the dishwasher won't run unless it confirms the door is fully closed and latched. After that: a failed control board, a tripped thermal fuse, or a power supply issue. On newer dishwashers with electronic controls, error codes point directly to the failed component. We carry door latch assemblies for the major brands and can usually resolve a no-start issue on the first visit."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "When does it make sense to repair vs replace a dishwasher?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Rule of thumb: under 8 years old and the repair is under $300, fix it. Over 10 years old AND the repair is over $400, consider replacing. Luxury brands (Miele, Bosch 800-series, Thermador, Cove) are almost always worth repairing, they're built for 15-20 year service lives and replacement runs $1,800–$3,500+ before installation. We tell you straight which side of that line your unit falls on."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What does the 90-day warranty cover?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Every dishwasher repair we complete carries a 90-day warranty on both parts and labor. If the same issue returns within that window, we come back at no charge. That's in writing before we leave."
