      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "My dishwasher leaves dishes dirty even on a full cycle, is that a spray arm issue?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Possibly. Clogged spray arm ports are common across SoCal due to hard water mineral deposits, the small holes that jet water onto your dishes gradually fill with calcium buildup and water pressure drops. It could also be a failing wash pump not building enough pressure, a clogged filter restricting water flow, or a detergent dispenser that isn't opening at the right point in the cycle. We check all of these systematically rather than replacing parts on a guess."
      }
