<!-- 03 INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="intro-grid">
      <div class="intro-body">
        <p class="section-number">01, About This Service</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">A dishwasher that doesn't work is one of those daily irritants that compounds fast.</h2>

        <p>Dishes pile up. You run a cycle anyway hoping it fixes itself. It doesn't. By day three the kitchen looks like a different household. We know the pattern well, dishwasher calls are one of the more consistent parts of what we do across SoCal. From a Pasadena family kitchen to a Newport Beach panel-ready Miele to a Thousand Oaks suburban Bosch to a Riverside Inland-Empire KitchenAid, the failure modes are predictable enough that our technicians can usually tell you what's wrong before they open the door.</p>

        <p>Standing water after a cycle is almost always the drain pump or a blocked filter. Door won't latch, the machine won't start, is usually the door latch assembly, one of the more common failures on every brand. Dishes coming out dirty points to spray arm ports clogged with mineral deposits, a failing wash pump, or a detergent dispenser that isn't opening at the right moment in the cycle.</p>

        <p>Across Southern California, hard water adds a layer to every dishwasher call. SoCal municipal water, LADWP, MWD, Calleguas, Santa Margarita, Rancho California, is high in calcium and magnesium, harder than most US cities. That mineral content accumulates in spray arm ports, coats the filter, builds up on the heating element, and leaves white film on glasses. Sometimes what looks like a dishwasher malfunction is the water, not the machine. Our technicians know how to distinguish between the two.</p>

        <div class="tip-box">
          <div class="tip-label">🔩 Filter Maintenance, Most Neglected Task</div>
          <p>The filter at the bottom of your dishwasher tub catches food debris and should be rinsed every one to two weeks. In SoCal's hard water environment it accumulates mineral deposits on top of food particles and blocks faster than in softer-water cities. A clogged filter restricts drain flow, reduces wash pressure, and causes standing water, all symptoms that look like a broken dishwasher but are actually maintenance issues. We clean the filter on every service call.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="tip-blue">
          <div class="tip-label">🏠 Panel-Ready Dishwashers</div>
          <p>Many kitchens across SoCal, Beverly Hills, Newport Coast, Pacific Palisades, Pasadena estates, and renovated homes from West Hills to Temecula wine country, have panel-ready dishwashers, the machine hidden behind a custom cabinet door matching the cabinetry. Accessing these for repair requires removing the panel without damaging the finish or the mounting hardware. Our technicians handle panel-ready units from Miele, Bosch, Thermador, Gaggenau, and Cove regularly and know the correct disassembly sequence for each.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

