    <h2 class="section-title">Custom panel dishwashers, we know how to work in them</h2>
    <p class="lead">A significant portion of dishwasher calls in Beverly Hills, Bel Air, Pacific Palisades, Newport Coast, San Marino, and renovated homes across SoCal involve panel-ready units. Most repair companies either avoid them or don't know the correct access procedure.</p>

    <div class="panel-block">
      <div class="panel-label">🏆 Panel-Ready Repair</div>
      <h3>The difference between a clean repair and a damaged cabinet</h3>
      <p>Panel-ready dishwashers have a custom cabinet door, typically matching the surrounding cabinetry, attached to the machine's door frame. Accessing the door components (latch, hinge, gasket, control panel) requires removing this panel correctly. Done wrong, the mounting hardware strips, the panel finish cracks, or the alignment changes when it's reinstalled.</p>
      <p>Our technicians access panel-ready dishwashers routinely. We know the disassembly sequence for Miele, Bosch, Thermador, Gaggenau, and Cove, the brands most frequently spec'd in SoCal high-end kitchens, and we bring the appropriate tools so the panel comes off cleanly and goes back on aligned.</p>
