<!-- 11 FAQ -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">09, Frequently Asked Questions</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Dishwasher repair, what people ask us</h2>

    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>How much does dishwasher repair cost?</h3>
        <p>Our diagnostic fee is $89, applied toward the repair once you approve the work. Most dishwasher repairs run between $120 and $280. A door latch, water inlet valve, or detergent dispenser replacement is toward the lower end. Control board or wash pump replacements on premium brands like Miele, Bosch, or Thermador run higher. We give you a full written estimate before any work begins.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Which areas of Southern California do you cover?</h3>
        <p>All five counties: Los Angeles, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, and Riverside. We dispatch from 8 service territories, West Hollywood (HQ), Los Angeles, Beverly Hills, Pasadena, Thousand Oaks, Irvine, Rancho Cucamonga, and Temecula, so the technician on your call is coming from the closest one. From Newport Beach to Pasadena to Thousand Oaks to Temecula, same-day is our standard.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>My dishwasher has standing water after the cycle, what's wrong?</h3>
        <p>Standing water after a cycle almost always points to the drain pump, either a failed pump motor or a clog in the pump filter or drain hose. In SoCal's hard water environment, mineral deposits can coat the filter and pump components, accelerating buildup. We clean the filter and check the pump before any parts are replaced.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Why do my dishes come out cloudy or with a white film?</h3>
        <p>Across Southern California, this is almost always a hard water issue, not a dishwasher malfunction. SoCal municipal water has high mineral content, calcium and magnesium deposits leave a white film on glassware over time. We inspect the spray arm ports, inlet valve screen, and detergent dispenser to make sure the machine is functioning correctly, then advise on whether rinse aid or a citric acid maintenance cycle would address the residue.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Do you repair panel-ready and integrated dishwashers?</h3>
        <p>Yes. Panel-ready dishwashers with custom cabinet fronts are common in Beverly Hills, Newport Coast, Pacific Palisades, and renovated homes across SoCal. We know the correct procedure for removing the door panel without damaging cabinetry, and we're familiar with the premium brands most often spec'd in these installations: Miele, Bosch, Thermador, Cove, and Gaggenau.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>My dishwasher won't start, what are the most common causes?</h3>
        <p>The door latch is the most frequent culprit, the dishwasher won't run unless it confirms the door is fully closed and latched. After that: a failed control board, a tripped thermal fuse, or a power supply issue. On newer dishwashers with electronic controls, error codes point directly to the failed component. We carry door latch assemblies for the major brands.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>When does it make sense to repair vs replace a dishwasher?</h3>
        <p>Rule of thumb: under 8 years old and the repair is under $300, fix it. Over 10 years old AND the repair is over $400, consider replacing. Luxury brands (Miele, Bosch 800-series, Thermador, Cove) are almost always worth repairing, they're built for 15-20 year service lives and replacement runs $1,800–$3,500+ before installation. We tell you straight which side of that line your unit falls on.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What does the 90-day warranty cover?</h3>
        <p>Every dishwasher repair we complete carries a 90-day warranty on both parts and labor. If the same issue returns within that window, we come back at no charge. That's in writing before we leave.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>My dishwasher leaves dishes dirty even on a full cycle, is that a spray arm issue?</h3>
        <p>Possibly. Clogged spray arm ports are common across SoCal due to hard water mineral deposits. It could also be a failing wash pump, a clogged filter restricting water flow, or a detergent dispenser that isn't opening at the right point in the cycle. We check all of these systematically rather than replacing parts on a guess.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

